Watch on youtube: https://youtu.be/9vhfI9yvmpU Tags: 3dprint , polymaker , material test , tpu filament , In this video all Polymaker TPU filaments are tested and compared with each other: TPU90 is the softest. TPU95 is hardest and HF means high flow, it can be printed on higher speeds. This is first detailed TPU test on Mytechfun channel, and suggestions about testing methods are welcome. Links to tested products (with same color): TPU90 blue (teal): https://us.polymaker.com/products/polyflex-tpu90?variant=39574341189689&aff=49 TPU95 orange: https://us.polymaker.com/products/polyflex-tpu95?variant=39574341386297&aff=49 TPU95-HF (black): https://us.polymaker.com/products/polyflex-tpu95-hf?aff=49 Results can be downloaded from the bottom of this page. On same place you can ind tested objects too (STL).
